<subSubSection pageId="36" pageNumber="437" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="36.[151,1437,1361,2034]" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1361,1386]" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[281,482,1361,1385]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mirabilis">
<emphasis box="[281,482,1361,1385]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">Colletes mirabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
cannot be assigned to any of the 
<taxonomicName box="[866,958,1361,1385]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[866,958,1361,1385]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">Colletes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-groups. Due the dense yellowishwhite pilosity that covers most of the body in both male and female and its size 
<taxonomicName box="[1039,1172,1397,1421]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mirabilis">
<emphasis box="[1039,1172,1397,1421]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">C. mirabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
reminds of a species of the 
<taxonomicName box="[193,349,1434,1457]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="squamosus">
<emphasis box="[193,349,1434,1457]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">C. squamosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group but the distinct dorsal incision of the male gonocoxite (secondarily fused in all species of the species-groups of 
<taxonomicName box="[421,568,1470,1493]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigricans">
<emphasis box="[421,568,1470,1493]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">C. nigricans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[590,737,1470,1493]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carinatus">
<emphasis box="[590,737,1470,1493]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">C. carinatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[759,940,1469,1493]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hylaeiformis">
<emphasis box="[759,940,1469,1493]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">C. hylaeiformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[963,1100,1470,1493]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caspicus">
<emphasis box="[963,1100,1470,1493]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">C. caspicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1171,1335,1470,1493]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="squamosus">
<emphasis box="[1171,1335,1470,1493]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">C. squamosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) clearly contradicts this assumption. Morphologically 
<taxonomicName box="[676,813,1505,1529]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mirabilis">
<emphasis box="[676,813,1505,1529]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">C. mirabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is isolated and the male can easily recognized by the characteristic shape of S 
<number box="[421,435,1542,1566]" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" value="7.0">7</number>
(
<figureCitation box="[451,515,1541,1566]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1416,1438]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,364,1393]" captionTargetId="figure@37.[151,1436,363,1395]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 8. Colletes mirabilis Kuhlmann &amp; Proshchalykin sp. nov., female: a. specimen, lateral view; b. head; c. scutum and scutellum; d. metasomal terga 1 and 2. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248254/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">
Fig. 
<number box="[502,515,1542,1566]" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
c) and the unique pilosity of the discs of T 
<number box="[984,1027,1542,1566]" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" value="3.0" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="2.0">2–4</number>
(
<figureCitation box="[1041,1107,1541,1566]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1416,1438]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,364,1393]" captionTargetId="figure@37.[151,1436,363,1395]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 8. Colletes mirabilis Kuhlmann &amp; Proshchalykin sp. nov., female: a. specimen, lateral view; b. head; c. scutum and scutellum; d. metasomal terga 1 and 2. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248254/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">
Fig. 
<number box="[1093,1107,1542,1566]" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
a, b). The discs are free of the thick yellowish-white, appressed appressed hair but instead are densely covered with very fine and short erect hairs that make the discs appear yellowish to greyish while the sculpture of the terga is still visible. This is unique among all 
<taxonomicName box="[191,283,1649,1673]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[191,283,1649,1673]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">Colletes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species known to us. The female is characterized by T 
<number box="[947,988,1650,1674]" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" value="2.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="1.0">1–4</number>
densely and completely covered with appressed yellowish-white hairs (
<figureCitation box="[525,592,1685,1710]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1416,1438]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,364,1393]" captionTargetId="figure@37.[151,1436,363,1395]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 8. Colletes mirabilis Kuhlmann &amp; Proshchalykin sp. nov., female: a. specimen, lateral view; b. head; c. scutum and scutellum; d. metasomal terga 1 and 2. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248254/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">
Fig. 
<number box="[578,592,1686,1710]" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
a, d) and the very large pair of apical clypeal depressions (
<figureCitation box="[1245,1311,1685,1710]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1416,1438]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,364,1393]" captionTargetId="figure@37.[151,1436,363,1395]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 8. Colletes mirabilis Kuhlmann &amp; Proshchalykin sp. nov., female: a. specimen, lateral view; b. head; c. scutum and scutellum; d. metasomal terga 1 and 2. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248254/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">
Fig. 
<number box="[1297,1311,1685,1710]" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
b).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="37" lastPageNumber="438" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="36.[151,1437,1361,2034]" lastBlockId="37.[151,1436,151,320]" lastPageId="37" lastPageNumber="438" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,447,1721,1746]" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">Description. Female.</emphasis>
Bl = 9.5 mm. Head. Head wider than long. Integument black except part of mandible dark reddish-brown. Face except clypeus densely covered with long, yellowish-white, erect hairs, on vertex a bit darker (
<figureCitation box="[239,306,1793,1818]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1416,1438]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,364,1393]" captionTargetId="figure@37.[151,1436,363,1395]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 8. Colletes mirabilis Kuhlmann &amp; Proshchalykin sp. nov., female: a. specimen, lateral view; b. head; c. scutum and scutellum; d. metasomal terga 1 and 2. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248254/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">
Fig. 
<number box="[292,306,1794,1818]" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
a, b). Clypeus flat, without longitudinal median depression, supraclypeal area triangular and convex in profile. Clypeus relatively finely and densely punctate (i = 0.5d), apically coarser and more dispersed; surface between punctures smooth and shiny, large pair of apical clypeal depressions (
<figureCitation box="[1035,1101,1865,1890]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1416,1438]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,364,1393]" captionTargetId="figure@37.[151,1436,363,1395]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 8. Colletes mirabilis Kuhlmann &amp; Proshchalykin sp. nov., female: a. specimen, lateral view; b. head; c. scutum and scutellum; d. metasomal terga 1 and 2. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248254/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">
Fig. 
<number box="[1087,1101,1865,1890]" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
b). Malar area medially about 
<number box="[151,161,1902,1926]" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[171,187,1902,1926]" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" value="4.0">4</number>
as long as width of mandible base, finely punctate. Antenna black, ventrally dark reddish-brown. Mesosoma. Integument black. Mesoscutal disc impunctate, smooth and shiny. Scutellum largely impunctate, smooth and shiny (
<figureCitation box="[159,230,1973,1998]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1416,1438]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,364,1393]" captionTargetId="figure@37.[151,1436,363,1395]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 8. Colletes mirabilis Kuhlmann &amp; Proshchalykin sp. nov., female: a. specimen, lateral view; b. head; c. scutum and scutellum; d. metasomal terga 1 and 2. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248254/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">
Fig. 
<number box="[216,230,1974,1998]" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
c). Mesoscutum, mesepisternum and propodeum densely covered with long light yellowish-white, erect hairs (
<figureCitation box="[221,288,2009,2034]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1416,1438]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,364,1393]" captionTargetId="figure@37.[151,1436,363,1395]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 8. Colletes mirabilis Kuhlmann &amp; Proshchalykin sp. nov., female: a. specimen, lateral view; b. head; c. scutum and scutellum; d. metasomal terga 1 and 2. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248254/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">
Fig. 
<number box="[274,288,2010,2034]" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
a, c). Wings. Very slightly yellowish; wing venation yellowish-brown. Legs. Integument black to dark reddish-brown. Vestiture whitish to yellowish-white, scopa white. Metasoma. Integument black except depressed apical tergal margins reddish to yellowish translucent (
<figureCitation box="[802,874,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1416,1438]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,364,1393]" captionTargetId="figure@37.[151,1436,363,1395]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 8. Colletes mirabilis Kuhlmann &amp; Proshchalykin sp. nov., female: a. specimen, lateral view; b. head; c. scutum and scutellum; d. metasomal terga 1 and 2. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248254/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">
Fig. 
<number box="[860,874,188,213]" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
d). T 
<number box="[936,976,188,212]" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" value="2.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="1.0">1–4</number>
densely covered with short appressed, yellowish hairs, on T 
<number box="[392,402,224,248]" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" value="1.0">1</number>
additionally with a few long, erect yellowish-white hairs; apical tergal hair bands broad but mostly indistinguishable from discs; terga apically slightly but distinctly depressed (
<figureCitation box="[1119,1188,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1416,1438]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,364,1393]" captionTargetId="figure@37.[151,1436,363,1395]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 8. Colletes mirabilis Kuhlmann &amp; Proshchalykin sp. nov., female: a. specimen, lateral view; b. head; c. scutum and scutellum; d. metasomal terga 1 and 2. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248254/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">
Fig. 
<number box="[1174,1188,260,285]" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
d). Terga densely and very finely punctate (i &lt;0.5d), between punctures smooth and shiny (
<figureCitation box="[930,996,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1416,1438]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,364,1393]" captionTargetId="figure@37.[151,1436,363,1395]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 8. Colletes mirabilis Kuhlmann &amp; Proshchalykin sp. nov., female: a. specimen, lateral view; b. head; c. scutum and scutellum; d. metasomal terga 1 and 2. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248254/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">
Fig. 
<number box="[982,996,295,320]" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
d).
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248254/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" targetBox="[151,1436,364,1393]" targetPageId="37">
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1435,1416,1469]" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,275,1416,1438]" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">FIGURE 8.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Kuhlmann &amp; Proshchalykin" authorityName="Kuhlmann &amp; Proshchalykin" box="[282,756,1416,1438]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mirabilis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[282,463,1416,1438]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">Colletes mirabilis</emphasis>
Kuhlmann &amp; Proshchalykin
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[763,844,1416,1438]" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[763,844,1416,1438]" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, female: a. specimen, lateral view; b. head; c. scutum and scutellum; d. metasomal terga 1 and 2. Scale bar: 1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1437,1508,2037]" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">
<collectingCountry box="[199,260,1508,1533]" name="Malta" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">Male</collectingCountry>
. Bl = 8.5 mm. Head. Head wider than long. Integument black except part of mandible dark reddishbrown. Face densely covered with long, yellowish-white, erect hairs. Malar area medially about 
<number box="[1273,1284,1545,1569]" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[1294,1308,1545,1569]" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" value="3.0">3</number>
as long as width of mandible base, finely striate. Antenna black, ventrally dark brown. Mesosoma. Integument black. Mesoscutal disc between punctures smooth and shiny; disc sparsely punctate (i = 1.5–2.0d) with small punctures. Scutellum anteriorly impunctate but with dense punctation apically, surface smooth and shiny. Mesoscutum, scutellum, metanotum, mesepisternum and propodeum covered with long, yellowish-white erect hairs (
<figureCitation box="[1338,1407,1688,1713]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1416,1438]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,364,1393]" captionTargetId="figure@37.[151,1436,363,1395]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 8. Colletes mirabilis Kuhlmann &amp; Proshchalykin sp. nov., female: a. specimen, lateral view; b. head; c. scutum and scutellum; d. metasomal terga 1 and 2. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248254/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">
Fig. 
<number box="[1393,1407,1689,1713]" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
a). Wings. Slightly yellowish-brown; wing venation yellowish-brown. Legs. Integument black, base and tips of tibias and barsitarsi reddish-brown and other tarsomeres yellowish-brown. Vestiture white. Metasoma. Integument black except depressed apical tergal margins reddish to yellowish translucent (
<figureCitation box="[1022,1095,1796,1821]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1416,1438]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,364,1393]" captionTargetId="figure@37.[151,1436,363,1395]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 8. Colletes mirabilis Kuhlmann &amp; Proshchalykin sp. nov., female: a. specimen, lateral view; b. head; c. scutum and scutellum; d. metasomal terga 1 and 2. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248254/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">
Fig. 
<number box="[1081,1095,1796,1821]" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
b). T 
<number box="[1160,1170,1797,1821]" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" value="1.0">1</number>
densely covered with yellowish-white short appressed hairs and with much longer erect hairs; discs of T 
<number box="[1088,1130,1833,1857]" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" value="3.0" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="2.0">2–4</number>
densely covered with very fine and short erect hairs that make the discs appear yellowish to greyish while the sculpture of the terga is still visible; rest of terga densely covered with short appressed yellowish-white hairs (
<figureCitation box="[1076,1144,1904,1929]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1416,1438]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,364,1393]" captionTargetId="figure@37.[151,1436,363,1395]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 8. Colletes mirabilis Kuhlmann &amp; Proshchalykin sp. nov., female: a. specimen, lateral view; b. head; c. scutum and scutellum; d. metasomal terga 1 and 2. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248254/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">
Fig. 
<number box="[1130,1144,1904,1929]" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
b); apical tergal hair band on T 
<number box="[212,222,1941,1965]" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" value="1.0">1</number>
narrow, on following terga broad but irregularly shaped (
<figureCitation box="[920,992,1940,1965]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1416,1438]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,364,1393]" captionTargetId="figure@37.[151,1436,363,1395]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 8. Colletes mirabilis Kuhlmann &amp; Proshchalykin sp. nov., female: a. specimen, lateral view; b. head; c. scutum and scutellum; d. metasomal terga 1 and 2. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248254/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">
Fig. 
<number box="[978,992,1940,1965]" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
b). Terga apically deeply and sharply depressed. Terga with very dense and fine punctation (i &lt;0.5d), between punctures smooth and shiny (
<figureCitation box="[1337,1406,1976,2001]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1416,1438]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,364,1393]" captionTargetId="figure@37.[151,1436,363,1395]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 8. Colletes mirabilis Kuhlmann &amp; Proshchalykin sp. nov., female: a. specimen, lateral view; b. head; c. scutum and scutellum; d. metasomal terga 1 and 2. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248254/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">
Fig. 
<number box="[1392,1406,1976,2001]" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
b). Terminalia. Genitalia and S 
<number box="[458,472,2013,2037]" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" value="7.0">7</number>
as illustrated (
<figureCitation box="[637,713,2012,2037]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1416,1438]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,364,1393]" captionTargetId="figure@37.[151,1436,363,1395]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 8. Colletes mirabilis Kuhlmann &amp; Proshchalykin sp. nov., female: a. specimen, lateral view; b. head; c. scutum and scutellum; d. metasomal terga 1 and 2. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248254/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">
